                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>JAMES WILLIAM FRENCH. On the 12th of July, about a quarter past ten o'clock at night, I was walking in<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182509150100"></xptr>
                  <placeName id="t18250915-269-crimeloc1445">Wardour-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-269-crimeloc1445" type="placeName" value="Wardour-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-269-crimeloc1445" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-269-off1443 t18250915-269-crimeloc1445"></join>, a person accosted me, and said I had lost my handkerchief - the officer afterwards produced it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-269-person1357">
                  ANGELIOUS 
                  BERTRAM
               <interp inst="t18250915-269-person1357" type="surname" value="BERTRAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-269-person1357" type="given" value="ANGELIOUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-269-person1357" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the three prisoners in St. Martin's-court - they followed the prosecutor through Leicester-square, Princes-street, and into Wardour street. I then saw Keith take the handkerchief - he and Anderson ran into Tyler's-court. I ran and took Benson at the corner of the court - Reardon took the other two in the court. I went into the public-house, and saw the handkerchief in Reardon's hand.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-269-person1358">
                  DANIEL 
                  REARDON
               <interp inst="t18250915-269-person1358" type="surname" value="REARDON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-269-person1358" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-269-person1358" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Bertram. I saw the three prisoners together for about ten minutes, or a quarter of an hour; they followed the prosecutor a little distance, and when they got near Tyler's-court, I saw Keith and Anderson rush into the court. I took Keith, and then Anderson, and the moment I took Anderson, I saw this handkerchief drop - Benson was at the end of the court.</p>
               <p>Prisoner BENSON. Q. How long was I with the other prisoners? A. About ten minutes.</p>
               <p>ANDERSON'S Defence. I was going to Mr. Jones, in Wardour-street for work. I met Keith, and a man came and took us.</p>


               <p>BENSON'S Defence. I was going along Wardour-street, and met Keith. I stood and spoke to him a minute or two, and was going away, when I was taken, on the contrary side of the way to the other two.</p>
               <p>KEITH'S Defence. I was walking down Wardour-street - the man took me and threw me on the ground.</p>
               <p>ANDERSON - <rs id="t18250915-269-verdict1446" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250915-269-verdict1446" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 15.</p>
               <p>KEITH - <rs id="t18250915-269-verdict1447" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250915-269-verdict1447" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 14.</p>
